Listing 5.3: Device identity, network endpoints, JWT state, relay state trackers, and tuning

constants (, lines 1946).

labId and deviceId are the identiers that the backend uses to look up which laboratory this

ESP32 belongs to and which device record to authenticate against. They are compiled-in integer

literals in the current build, which means reashing is required to deploy the same rmware binary

to a second laboratory with a dierent ID  a maintainability gap noted in Chapter 6 and tracked

against NFR-MAIN-01.

The three API endpoint strings embed the local network IP address 192.168.1.7 and port 5076,

which are the host:port of the.NET Core backend process on the development network. serverUrl

points to the motion-event endpoint; lightApi points to an endpoint used for direct light-state

queries (reserved for future use); TokenGen points to the device authentication endpoint.

jwtToken and tokenExpireMillis implement the client side of the JWT caching strategy:

after a successful token exchange, jwtToken holds the bearer token string and tokenExpireMillis

holds the millis() value at which the rmware will proactively refresh it. lastLightState and

lastFanState are the dierential-update guards that prevent unnecessary relay switching chatter

a relay is only toggled when the commanded state diers from the last applied state.

DISTANCE\_THRESHOLD (50 cm) denes the boundary within which the HC-SR04 considers a

COOLDOWN (2000 ms) is the minimum gap between consecutive

person to be near the sensor.

motion-event POSTs, preventing the rmware from ooding the backend if a person lingers near the

sensor. LIGHT\_THRESHOLD (2000) is the ADC reading below which the local fallback logic considers

the room too dark to leave the light o. LIGHT\_INTERVAL is declared but currently unused  it was

intended for a periodic light-level check independent of motion events, which remains as planned

